D.  Individual Rights
When we rely on consent to use your personal information, or as otherwise required by applicable law, you have the right to withdraw consent, to object processing, to refuse automated individual decision-making, to make corrections or supplements, to restrict our processing your personal information, or to request us to delete your personal information collected directly from you unless we need it for legally permissible purposes. In addition, where processing of your personal information is carried out by automated means, you have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format or, where technically feasible, to transfer your personal data to another company.
Please contact us Data Protection Officer at  support@joilive.net if you would like to exercise your rights under applicable law. When we receive an individual rights request from you, please make sure you are ready to verify your identity. We may limit your individual rights in the following ways:
Where denial of access is required or authorized by law;
When granting access would have a negative impact on other's privacy;
To protect our rights and properties; and
Where the request is frivolous or burdensome.
15.  How to Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the Services, please contact us at  support@joilive.net, with a copy to: legal@joilive.net.